Gary L. Castagna: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 23, 2017 10:37 PM ET
Chemicals

Company Overview of Minerals Technologies Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Gary L. Castagna  Group President of Performance Materials, Minerals Technologies Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 5 different industries.55$2,168,416As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Gary L. Castagna has been Group President of Performance Materials at Minerals Technologies Inc. since May 9, 2017 and served as its Group President for Performance Materials and Construction Technologies since March 15, 2017 until May 9, 2017. Mr. Castagna served as Senior Vice President and Managing Director of Performance Materials at Minerals Technologies Inc. from June 2014 to March 15, 2017. Mr. Castagna served as the Chief Operating Officer at AMCOL International ... Corporation since January 1, 2014. He served as an Executive Vice President of AMCOL International Corporation (AMCOL) since January 1, 2014 and President of Performance Materials Segment since May 2008. He served as the President of AMCOL Health & Beauty Solutions, Inc. He served as the President of Global Minerals & Materials and Senior Vice President of Amcol International Corp., since May 2008 and February 2001 respectively. He served as Treasurer of AMCOL International Corp. since February 2001 and served as its Chief Accounting Officer. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of AMCOL International Corp. from February 2001 to May 2008. He served as a Consultant to AMCOL from June 2000 to February 2001 and Vice President of AMCOL International Corp. He served as the President of Chemdal International Corp., (this business, a former subsidiary of AMCOL, consisted of the absorbent polymers business that was sold to BASF AG in June 2000) from August 1997 to May 2000. He served as Vice President of Chemical International Corporation, a former subsidiary of Amcol, from August 1997 to May 2000. Prior thereto, he served as Vice President of Finance for Chemdal International Corp. He served as a Non Executive Director of Ashapura Minechem Limited until May 2009. He served as a Director of Green St. Energy, Inc. (a/k/a M-Wave Inc.) from January 2001 to January 2009. Mr. Castagna received his Bachelor's Degree in Accounting and Finance from the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor and has also completed Graduate Courses and is a Certified Public Accountant. Mr. Castagna holds a degree in accounting from Lake Superior State University.Read Full Background




